KRT Beta Rail Transit Mod

Mod Introduction

This is a Kunming Rail Transit themed mod developed for the Minecraft Fabric platform, featuring subway tracks, signaling systems, station buildings, and other elements that allow players to experience and build their own subway system in the game.

Inventory Description

The mod includes two main inventory categories:

Tracks & Control Items

• Subway Track: Basic track block for laying subway lines

• Switch Track: Track block that can change direction

• Signal Machine: Device for controlling train operations

• ATP Signal Machine: Advanced Train Protection system signal device

• Announcement System: Device for playing station broadcasts

• Line Configuration Panel: Panel for setting subway line information

• Train Control Panel: Panel for controlling train operations

• Driver Key: Key to activate the train control panel

• Screen Door Key: Key to open screen doors

Station Construction Items

• Screen Door: Safety doors on station platforms

• Platform Block: Basic block for station platforms

• Station Train Arrival Countdown Display: Screen showing arrival time of next train

• Small TV: Small display showing various information

Block Function Description

Track System

• Subway Track: Basic track block supporting minecarts and trains

• Switch Track: Can change track direction to enable train switching

Signaling System

• Signal Machine: Displays red, yellow, and green signals to control train movement

• ATP Signal Machine: Advanced signaling system providing additional train protection

Station Equipment

• Screen Door: Generates safety doors on station platforms, requires screen door key to open

• Announcement System: Broadcast device for station arrival information

• Platform Block: Basic construction material for station platforms

Control Devices

• Line Configuration Panel: Sets subway line names, station lists, and destination information

• Train Control Panel: Controls train startup, stopping, acceleration, and deceleration; requires driver key to activate

• Station Train Arrival Countdown Display: Shows estimated arrival time of next train

• Small TV: Small display showing train schedules, announcements, and other information

Usage Instructions

Building Subway Lines

1. Lay tracks using subway tracks and switch tracks
2. Place signal machines at key locations to control train operations
3. Set up station areas at line terminals or intermediate points

Constructing Stations

1. Build station platforms using platform blocks
2. Install screen doors for safety
3. Place announcement systems, countdown displays, and small TVs
4. Configure line information using the line configuration panel

Controlling Trains

1. Right-click the train control panel with driver key to enter driving mode
2. Use W key to move forward, S key to move backward
3. Use A key to switch gears
4. Use E key to toggle between automatic (ATO) and manual control modes
5. Use ESC key to exit driving mode

Notes

• Trains can only run on tracks and cannot move on regular blocks

• Signal machines and ATP signal machines require proper connections to function

• Screen doors and train control panels require corresponding keys to activate

• Some advanced features require server mode for full functionality

